<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujtiel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jtiel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://jtiel.tripod.ca/j.gif" BORDER=0> at: 10/22/01 12:02:22 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usquinkmcpoke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Squink McPoke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/4/01 2:05:36 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: John Smedley - Reviewing Customer Service at Verant</span><hr size=1> Few points to consider:<br>
<br>
a) I would take EQ subscription numbers with a grain of salt, as I am sure many many people pay for 3 or 6 months at a time.  So technically they are still a subscriber, though they may have left and won't be renewing.  Time will tell.<br>
<br>
b) With Verant, and their history, coincidences do not exist.  They had 2+ years to recognize and fix their HORRIBLE CS, we as players have been griping about this, publicly, for a long long long time.  Why suddenly now is it a huge priority?<br>
<br>
c) As posted in rant hall a while back, the CEO of SOE has described us as credit cards with legs.  According to him, listening to us only @#%$ them up.  Gee, thanks Mr. Flock.<br>
<br>
d) Better CS != throwing newer phatter lewt at us to distract us for a while (coughSOLcough).  Better CS to me means getting a timely, helpful reply to a request for assistance with bugs, harassment, etc.  Not having someone KS a mob you need for a quest, repeatedly over the span of 2 hours, then having a GM show up and say basically 'too bad, you are SOL' (fitting acronym).  This is all without the 'play nice policies' that were <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> supposed</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to be enforced in situations like this.  Trust me the last thing I want to have to do is petition for help with a conflict with my fellow players.  But I expect that when/if I have to, that THEIR OWN POLICIES will be enforced.  Else why even have them in the first place?<br>
<br>
e) Did I mention Mr. Flock is an @#%$?  And he is the boss of everyone at Verant if I'm not mistaken.  It starts at the top...<br>
<br>
f) No I don't think they sit in a dark room plotting against me.  I think they sit in a dark room with their fingers in their ears chanting &quot;nah nah nah I can't hear you, everything is juuuuust fine&quot;.<br>
<br>
g) I *really really like* the GAME everquest.  I *really really dislike* some of the public figures representing the game, and their shoddy excuse for customer service.<br>
<br>
h) I emailed all of the above points to the email presented by John Smedley the day after I was made aware that they wanted customer input.  I got a form mail returned to me (expected) and to this day there has been no public recognition that they have been doing anything with all the feedback that they got.  And in asking around and reading various boards, it appears that all this feedback merely resulted in a 'search and replace' command on their reimbursement policies.<br>
